Four blasts heard near London Bridge
Share this article with Google Plus
Four explosions have been heard near London Bridge, reports say.
Witnesses reported hearing two explosions near London bridge and one near Borough Market.
Police are yet to confirm whether they are controlled explosions.
MORE: London Bridge incident is ‘potential act of terrorism’, says Theresa May
Up to seven people are feared dead after a gang of five terrorists drove a van into pedestrians on London Bridge.
The group then attacked crowds with large knives, it has been claimed.
Police at the cordon at the south side of London Bridge told BBC there is more than one fatality.
As many as seven are feared dead.
Armed police, who have confirmed the attack is ‘terror related’, are currently at the scene.